        i went to see good kid in leeds!

        so for those unaware, good kid are a canadian indie-rock band whose most streamed songs include no time to explain, mimis delivery service, and a cover of from the start by laufey. theyve brought their tour to the uk and in january i was lucky enough to nab tickets during the presale. after 8 months of eagerly waiting, the day finally arrived, and i took my stepdad with me because my friend and cousin were unavailable; he liked the sound of the band, comparing them to the kooks.

        traffic held me up so i missed the first two songs of dutch criminal records setlist. but from then on it was a blast!! dcr were a lot of fun already, and the sound engineer got us to do the hot to go! dance after i went down to the floor area. then the show started and my serotonin levels were on the rise. good kid had so much charisma, the crowd were amazing, the gig was interactive as , etc. with a bar in the venue, i had to move back up to the balcony because it was hot down there and i needed a drink, but i still had a great view. and the wheel of chaos was incredible as per usual - i have a tiktok of this uploaded, you can hear some lads egging them to spin it before they had a chance to explain

        favourite night of the year? it might very well be, because the post-concert blues are hitting. but this is a band i would happily see again and again, they were fantastic and it was well worth the wait
